Subject: Toribrot

Description: Normalized refinement of the Toribrot definition as a recursive toroidal subject architecture. This file preserves the distinction between the geometric model, the deformation-frame analysis, and any downstream physics interpretation.

@ [source] C:/Users/jerem/Downloads/toribrot_sop_definition.md
@ [source] platform/refinement/Delineation.sop
@ [source] platform/refinement/Observer_Honesty_Security.sop
@ [source] platform/source/SOP_Markdown.md

& [Toribrot] is a recursive toroidal subject architecture formed from intrinsic torus dynamics, pants decomposition, winding convergence, and deformation modifiers
  + [base_surface] is a complex torus or elliptic curve carrying the primary continuity field
  + [lattice] is the generating period structure of the torus
  + [intrinsic_map] is a self-map of the torus that generates winding, translation, expansion, contraction, or recurrence
  + [pants_unit] is a local pair-of-pants domain embedded in the torus and used as a bounded decomposition/composition operator
  + [pants_composition_graph] is the directed graph of pants-unit gluing, flow, and recursive composition
  + [metric_texture_field] is the evolving scalar, vector, or tensor field carried by torus dynamics
  + [winding_field] is the family of recurrent paths generated by intrinsic maps and boundary flows
  + [convergence_point] is a region where windings, texture, curvature, or phase concentrate toward an apparent terminal point
  + [door] is a convergence point treated as traversable rather than terminal
  + [recursive_layer] is the re-emergent toroidal field reached by passing through a door
  + [deformation_frame] is the local modifier basis governing how the shape compresses, twists, folds, opens, or changes across recursion
  + [modifier_count] is the observed or selected number of deformation axes in a frame
  + [uncertainty] is any unsupported, unproven, or unstable correspondence between the observed modifier frame and a formal mathematical group

  ? [use_when: modeling the original Toribrot emergence, recursive toroidal deformation, or SOP-form pants architecture]
    = must: preserve the torus, pants, winding, convergence, and recursive-door lineage
    = must: distinguish observed deformation behavior from formal group-theoretic proof
    = must: allow modifier frames other than ten when the shape requires more or fewer deformation axes
    = must: preserve [SO10Frame] as one historically important candidate, not as the closed scope of Toribrot

  - never: treat [SO10Frame] as exhaustive without deformation analysis
  - never: collapse recursive deformation into a fixed symbolic label
  - never: claim physical SO(10) equivalence unless a formal representation, invariant form, closure law, and Lie algebra correspondence are supplied

## Base Surface

& [ToribrotBaseSurface] is the continuous toroidal substrate on which Toribrot dynamics occur
  + [complex_torus] is C / Lambda for a rank-two lattice Lambda
  + [elliptic_curve_identity] is the identification of the complex torus with an elliptic curve when valid
  + [group_law] is the elliptic curve operation used by affine self-maps
  + [real_torus_model] is R^2 / Z^2 used for smooth toral automorphisms
  + [complex_structure] is the holomorphic structure preserved only by compatible maps
  + [smooth_structure] is the differentiable torus structure used when maps are not holomorphic

  = must: preserve whether a map is holomorphic, smooth, or only topological
  = must: keep complex elliptic-curve dynamics distinct from real SL(2,Z) dynamics

## Intrinsic Maps

& [ToribrotIntrinsicMap] is a torus self-map that generates recurrence, winding, translation, expansion, or deformation
  + [elliptic_affine_map] is f_{P,m}(Q) = [m]Q + P on an elliptic curve
  + [multiplication_degree] is m^2 for multiplication-by-m maps
  + [translation_point] is P in the elliptic curve group law
  + [toral_automorphism] is F_A induced by A in SL(2,Z) on R^2/Z^2
  + [hyperbolic_mode] is the case where A has eigenvalues lambda and lambda^-1 with |lambda| > 1
  + [expanding_direction] is the unstable winding direction
  + [contracting_direction] is the stable winding direction

  ? [map is elliptic_affine_map]
    = must: treat the map as holomorphic
    = must: treat the map as a group homomorphism only when P = 0

  ? [map is toral_automorphism]
    = must: treat the map as smooth unless complex-structure compatibility is proven
    = must: preserve stable and unstable directions

## Cell State and Transform Rule

& [ToribrotCellState] is the local dynamic state carried by a Toribrot cell during recursive curvature evolution
  + [kappa] is the local curvature state or curvature-defect accumulation
  + [theta] is the local orientation state of the cell frame
  + [rho] is the local compression density or packing-pressure accumulation
  + [phi] is the local winding phase transported through the toroidal frame
  + [state_vector] is ([kappa], [theta], [rho], [phi])

  = must: treat the cell as a dynamic state carrier, not only a static wedge
  = must: preserve units, angle conventions, and phase wrapping before numeric simulation

& [ToribrotTransformRule] is the recursive update law for a Toribrot cell state under local geometry, neighborhood coupling, and deformation modifiers
  + [input_state] is ([kappa], [theta], [rho], [phi]) before the update
  + [output_state] is ([kappa_prime], [theta_prime], [rho_prime], [phi_prime]) after the update
  + [cell_geometry] is the local angle, taper, thickness, orientation, and boundary shape
  + [packing_stress] is local boundary mismatch, compression, overlap, or gap pressure
  + [curvature_defect] is angular surplus or deficit around the relevant local junction
  + [neighbor_coupling] is the influence of adjacent cell states on the update
  + [modifier_frame] is the active deformation-frame basis applied during the update
  + [coefficient_set] is the selected weights controlling how each observable contributes to the update
  + [normalization] is angle wrapping, phase wrapping, density clamping, and curvature scale handling
  + [uncertainty] is any unsupported choice of coefficients, units, physical interpretation, or closure law

  ^ [ToribrotTransform] is T: ([kappa], [theta], [rho], [phi]) -> ([kappa_prime], [theta_prime], [rho_prime], [phi_prime])
    + [kappa_prime] is the curvature update derived from prior curvature, curvature defect, packing stress, compression density, and neighbor curvature coupling
    + [theta_prime] is the orientation update derived from prior orientation, winding phase, chirality, boundary turn, and neighbor orientation coupling
    + [rho_prime] is the compression-density update derived from prior density, packing stress, convergence pressure, expansion relief, and boundary fit
    + [phi_prime] is the winding-phase update derived from prior phase, winding increment, torsion, orientation change, and curvature coupling

    = must: define the coefficient set before numeric testing
    = must: define normalization before comparing iterations
    = must: keep recursive curvature evolution distinct from static wedge packing
    = must: preserve [uncertainty] when transform coefficients are chosen heuristically

  = must: use [ToribrotTransform] when studying recursive curvature evolution
  = must: treat static wedge geometry as input to the transform, not as the whole model
  - never: infer physical singularity behavior from the transform unless the physical mapping is separately derived

& [ToribrotTransformA0] is the first grounded transform candidate using a fixed hyperbolic toral automorphism as the recurrence generator
  + [base_map] is toral_automorphism induced by A in SL(2,Z)
  + [A] is [[2, 1], [1, 1]]
  + [state] is torus coordinate x in R^2/Z^2
  + [coefficient_set] is A0_cat_map_coefficients
  + [matrix_A] is [[2, 1], [1, 1]]
  + [determinant] is 1
  + [trace] is 3
  + [eigenvalues] are ((3 + sqrt(5)) / 2, (3 - sqrt(5)) / 2)
  + [expanding_direction] is the unstable eigenvector of A
  + [contracting_direction] is the stable eigenvector of A
  + [winding_density] is recurrence density under repeated application
  + [curvature_proxy] is local concentration or gradient of recurrence density
  + [scale_mapping] is normalized_dimensionless_torus_units
  + [coordinate_domain] is R^2 / Z^2
  + [unit_length] is one normalized torus period
  + [unit_time] is one transform iteration
  + [physical_units] is undefined
  + [status] is fixed_by_toral_automorphism_not_fitted

  = must: test recurrence and density before adding free coefficients
  = must: derive stress or curvature proxy from observed density, not assign it by hand
  = must: preserve stable and unstable directions
  = must: keep [physical_units] undefined until cross-scale validation supplies a mapping
  = must: use a compatible lattice or continuous torus coordinates before discretizing onto an unequal grid
  = must: reject direct 360 by 180 cell-index application unless lattice preservation is proven
  - never: introduce physical constants in A0

& [ToribrotTransformA0R] is a retired rectangular-grid control that tested a mistaken stacking of the 360 major-ring cells with the 180 perpendicular pancake layers
  + [base_map] is toral_automorphism induced by A in SL(2,Z)
  + [A] is [[3, 2], [1, 1]]
  + [state] is cell coordinate x in Z_360 by Z_180
  + [status] is retired_as_orientation_misfit
  + [fault] is treating non-stackable major-ring and pancake orientations as one rectangular index lattice

  = must: preserve A0R only as a control result showing what happens under the rectangular-grid assumption
  = must: prefer an oriented-foliation model for the Toribrot tessellation
  - never: use A0R as the active 360 by 180 Toribrot geometry without rejustifying the shared orientation assumption

& [ToribrotOrientedFoliationModel] is the corrected tessellation model where the 360 major-ring segments and 180 perpendicular pancake layers are distinct oriented components rather than a single rectangular product grid
  + [major_ring_foliation] is 360 one-degree Toribrot segments wrapping through the torus ring
  + [pancake_stack] is 180 alternating-face layers laid through the center of the torus hole perpendicular to the flat torus
  + [orientation_relation] is perpendicular or cross-oriented rather than stackable
  + [coupling_site] is the local intersection, crossing, or projection relation where major-ring state can interact with pancake-layer state
  + [major_state] is ([kappa_major], [theta_major], [rho_major], [phi_major])
  + [pancake_state] is ([kappa_pancake], [theta_pancake], [rho_pancake], [phi_pancake])
  + [coupled_state] is a relation between [major_state] and [pancake_state], not a rectangular coordinate pair
  + [uncertainty] is the unresolved local rule for coupling perpendicular states

  = must: preserve the orientation distinction between [major_ring_foliation] and [pancake_stack]
  = must: define coupling through an explicit projection, intersection, or boundary rule
  = must: test major and pancake dynamics separately before composing them
  - never: combine 360 and 180 as Z_360 by Z_180 unless a shared coordinate basis is explicitly defined
  - never: treat perpendicular pancake layers as ordinary minor-axis indices of a rectangular torus grid

## Pants Units

& [ToribrotPantsUnit] is a local pair-of-pants operation embedded in the torus
  + [domain] is a pair-of-pants surface embedded in an open subset of the torus
  + [boundary_component] is one of three circular interfaces
  + [input_boundary] is a boundary used as incoming flow or subject leg
  + [output_boundary] is a boundary used as outgoing flow or composed waist
  + [local_map] is the restriction of an intrinsic map or other valid local operation to the pants domain
  + [gluing_condition] is equality or collar-extendable boundary compatibility between adjacent units

  / [pants_unit] -(PantsDecomposition)> [input_boundary], [input_boundary], [output_boundary]
  * [input_boundary], [input_boundary] -(PantsComposition)> [output_boundary]

  = must: preserve boundary identity during gluing
  = must: block composition when boundary maps are incompatible

## Winding Convergence and Door Traversal

& [ToribrotWindingConvergence] is the pass that detects where recurrent torus paths concentrate into a possible recursive transition
  + [winding_path] is a curve generated by intrinsic maps, pants-boundary flow, or texture-field transport
  + [phase_density] is local accumulation of winding phase or recurrence
  + [metric_distortion] is local expansion, contraction, shear, torsion, or curvature proxy
  + [convergence_point] is a local attractor, vortex core, folded seam, or apparent endpoint of windings
  + [terminal_reading] is the interpretation of convergence as an endpoint
  + [door_reading] is the interpretation of convergence as a traversable interface
  + [door_pressure] is the operation of pushing through convergence rather than stopping at it
  + [recursive_reentry] is the emergence of another toroidal layer after door traversal

  ? [windings converge]
    = must: inspect whether convergence is terminal, periodic, singular, or traversable
    = must: preserve [terminal_reading] and [door_reading] as alternatives until tested
    = may: apply [DoorTraversal] when recursion is intended

^ [DoorTraversal] is the operation that reinterprets a convergence point as a recursive interface
  + [input] is a convergence point with winding accumulation
  + [compression_component] is the inward deformation required to enter the point
  + [twist_component] is the chiral deformation required to preserve orientation or transform it
  + [output] is a recursive layer, blocked transition, or uncertainty

  = must: pass through compression before re-emergence
  = must: account for chirality when orientation changes
  = must: emit uncertainty when the transition has no stable deformation frame

## Deformation Frame

& [ToribrotDeformationFrame] is a local basis of modifiers that describes how the toroidal shape changes under winding convergence, folding, recursion, and re-emergence
  + [modifier] is one independent deformation axis, operator, parameter, or observable mode
  + [compression_modifier] is a modifier governing inward motion, scale reduction, density, or recursive contraction
  + [chiral_modifier] is a modifier governing handedness, torsion, phase rotation, parity, or circulation bias
  + [fold_modifier] is a modifier governing seam folding, boundary gluing, or pants-interface inversion
  + [shear_modifier] is a modifier governing lateral displacement or anisotropic distortion
  + [stretch_modifier] is a modifier governing expansion, elongation, or unstable-direction growth
  + [translation_modifier] is a modifier governing affine displacement across the torus
  + [braid_modifier] is a modifier governing crossing, over-under relation, or path entanglement
  + [recursion_modifier] is a modifier governing depth, layer transition, or self-similar continuation
  + [closure_modifier] is a modifier governing cyclic reconnection or toroidal completion
  + [modifier_count] is derived from observed independent modifiers, not imposed in advance

  ? [constructing a deformation frame]
    = must: derive modifiers from observable deformation behavior where possible
    = must: separate compression, chirality, folding, shear, stretch, translation, braid, recursion, and closure unless evidence fuses them
    = must: preserve dependent modifiers as relations rather than independent axes
    = must: allow [modifier_count] to change under higher-resolution analysis

  - never: choose a modifier count only because a known group has that dimension
  - never: treat symbolic elegance as evidence of completeness

## Historical SO(10) Candidate

& [SO10Frame] is the historical ten-modifier Toribrot frame discovered as five compression modifiers and five chiral twist modifiers
  + [compression_set] is C1, C2, C3, C4, C5
  + [chiral_set] is X1, X2, X3, X4, X5
  + [modifier_count] is 10
  + [status] is lineage_preserved and provisionally_useful
  + [formal_status] is unproven unless orthogonal representation and closure are demonstrated

  + [C1_radial_compression] is inward contraction toward a convergence point
  + [C2_scale_recursion] is passage from one scale layer into a nested layer
  + [C3_boundary_folding] is inward folding of pants boundaries, seams, or edges
  + [C4_density_accumulation] is local concentration of texture, phase, or information
  + [C5_convergence_lock] is stabilization of a convergence point as a traversable door

  + [X1_handedness] is clockwise or counterclockwise orientation selection
  + [X2_torsion] is helical deformation of winding paths
  + [X3_phase_rotation] is angular offset during recursive traversal
  + [X4_parity_inversion] is mirror-flip behavior across a door
  + [X5_circulation_bias] is preservation, reversal, or compounding of winding flow

  ? [use_when: preserving the original Toribrot discovery lineage]
    = must: keep the 5 compression + 5 chiral split visible
    = must: mark SO(10) as a candidate frame rather than a completed proof

  ? [testing formal SO(10) correspondence]
    = must: define a 10-dimensional vector space of modifiers
    = must: define an invariant quadratic form
    = must: show modifier transformations preserve that form
    = must: show closure under composition
    = must: compare the resulting infinitesimal generators to so(10)

  - never: use [SO10Frame] to exclude additional deformation modes

## Modifier Count Discovery

^ [DiscoverModifierCount] is the procedure for deriving possible deformation-frame sizes from Toribrot behavior
  + [input] is winding, metric, texture, pants-boundary, and recursive-door behavior
  + [observable_mode] is a distinct deformation pattern that survives repeated analysis
  + [independent_axis] is a modifier that cannot be reconstructed from other modifiers under the chosen resolution
  + [dependent_relation] is a deformation that can be expressed as a combination, constraint, or effect of other modifiers
  + [candidate_frame] is a proposed modifier set and count
  + [evidence] is the reason the count is justified
  + [uncertainty] is unresolved dependence, hidden coupling, or missing deformation behavior

  = must: gather observable deformation modes before choosing a group label
  = must: test whether each mode is independent, derived, redundant, or coupled
  = must: produce at least one candidate frame and one uncertainty register
  = should: compare candidate counts against known symmetry structures only after deriving the modes

  - never: force the observed shape into SO(10), SO(n), SU(n), Spin(n), or another group before deriving the deformation axes

## Candidate Modifier Families Beyond Ten

& [ExpandedModifierFamilies] is the open set of deformation categories that may extend beyond the original SO10Frame
  + [compression] is inward scale, density, and convergence behavior
  + [expansion] is outward growth, unstable-direction stretch, or re-emergence behavior
  + [chirality] is handed twist, torsion, and orientation bias
  + [folding] is seam, edge, or boundary inversion behavior
  + [shear] is anisotropic skew or lateral deformation
  + [translation] is affine displacement or phase-shifted relocation
  + [braiding] is path entanglement, crossing order, and winding interlock
  + [reflection] is parity or mirror behavior not reducible to chirality
  + [recursion] is depth, nesting, self-similarity, and layer transition
  + [closure] is cyclic reconnection, toroidal sealing, or boundary disappearance
  + [metric] is length, area, curvature, or distortion-field behavior
  + [texture] is scalar or symbolic field transport over the surface

  ? [use_when: SO10Frame feels incomplete]
    = must: inspect which modifier families are missing from the ten-frame
    = must: decide whether missing families are independent axes or refinements of existing axes
    = must: emit a larger candidate frame when independence survives testing

## Candidate Frames To Explore

& [ToribrotCandidateFrames] is the set of modifier-count hypotheses to test
  + [Frame10_SO10Like] is 5 compression plus 5 chiral modifiers
  + [Frame12_GeometricFuller] is compression, expansion, chirality, folding, shear, translation, braiding, reflection, recursion, closure, metric, texture
  + [Frame15_PantsExpanded] is five compression, five chirality, and five pants-interface deformation modes
  + [Frame16_SpinorLike] is a candidate where recursive door traversal behaves like binary orientation branching across four paired choices
  + [Frame20_DoubleTen] is one ten-frame before the door and one transformed ten-frame after the door
  + [Frame45_FormalSO10Generators] is the generator-count frame of formal so(10), distinct from the ten-axis vector frame
  + [FrameN_Open] is an empirically derived modifier set with no assumed target count

  = must: distinguish vector dimension from generator dimension
  = must: distinguish observed deformation modifiers from formal symmetry generators
  = must: keep [FrameN_Open] available until deformation analysis closes
